title: A short story about Diamond division!

embed.description: Hello summoners! This is a new montage with moments from the ranked games and from the stream. If you need help from me, you can find me here or in other places like: 1. Twitter: https://twitter.com/IceManLucky 2. Twitchtv : www.twitch.tv/icemanlucky 3. Facebook fanpage: https://www.facebook.com/IceManLucky 4. askfm - ask.fm/DinescuLucian Enjoy your stay!

body: Hello! Here is a short story about Diamond division! I hope that you like it :D Enjoy!

replies.body:
1: .Rumble support actually works during the game you played

2: Dude explain why he plays it, look at the chat

3: You complain, even after it actually works.

4: "It was hard" Yeah, I am sure that the rumble who was actually trying was really hard to play with. I bet that double didn't help either. I would take I feeding janna over him anyday, amiright?

Seems like typical meta thumping elitism to me. No shit people are going to make bad plays, and miss hooks. Everyone does. Don't tell me you have never missed an ezreal or Jinx ulti? You never missed that Q?

Just because it is diamond doesn't mean people are going to make mistakes.

I don't really understand the message of this video? All I saw was "hurr I still have to carry some games even in diamond! look at all these missed hooks! look at this off meta pick!"
